  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Prevention of Trafficking in Persons, Comprehensive Assistance to Victims, Investigation, and Prosecution of the Crime in Colombia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM will contribute to the prevention of trafficking in persons, the comprehensive assistance to victims and the investigation and prosecution of the crime in Colombia. This initiative will implement activities related to three work areas aligned with the project outcomes: i) develop tools on prevention of trafficking in persons, addressed to prioritized populations, towards risk and vulnerability factors mitigation associated with this crime; ii) comprehensive assistance measures, emphasizing victims transferring and immediate assistance; and iii) strengthen knowledge and technical tools of local officials with competence in the investigation and prosecution of trafficking in persons through mock trials.</narrative>
  </description>
